From fa8fffa729247f6bf156e410dbd2f7c206128892 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2026 16:45:06 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 120/174] fs/userfaultfd: validate uffd ranges in MMUPAGE
 units, not PAGE units
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

userfaultfd is a userspace-visible interface; the granularity of all
range arguments (UFFDIO_REGISTER, UFFDIO_UNREGISTER, UFFDIO_COPY,
UFFDIO_ZEROPAGE, UFFDIO_WAKE, UFFDIO_WRITEPROTECT) is the userspace
page size, which equals sysconf(_SC_PAGESIZE).

Under PGCL (CONFIG_PAGE_MMUSHIFT > 0), the userspace page size is
MMUPAGE_SIZE (the hardware MMU page size), while the kernel PAGE_SIZE
is MMUPAGE_SIZE << CONFIG_PAGE_MMUSHIFT.  The PAGE_MASK / MMUPAGE_MASK
divergence breaks validate_unaligned_range / validate_range:

  - Userspace mmaps 10 * sysconf(_SC_PAGESIZE) = 10 * MMUPAGE_SIZE.
  - Userspace calls UFFDIO_REGISTER with len = 10 * MMUPAGE_SIZE.
  - Kernel checks `len & ~PAGE_MASK` and the low MMUPAGE-sized bits
    of len are non-zero (10 * MMUPAGE_SIZE is not a multiple of
    PAGE_SIZE when PAGE_MMUCOUNT > 1).
  - UFFDIO_REGISTER returns -EINVAL.

Visible in tools/testing/selftests/mm/guard-regions.c uffd subtest:

  not ok 13 guard_regions.anon.uffd
  not ok 43 guard_regions.shmem.uffd

on s390x PGCL=4 (CONFIG_USERFAULTFD=y).  s390x mainline and PGCL=0
pass — those have PAGE_MASK == MMUPAGE_MASK so the bug is invisible.
Arches whose defconfig sets CONFIG_USERFAULTFD=n (aarch64, ppc64,
many others) SKIP the uffd subtest and don't observe this directly.
loongarch64 PGCL=2/4/6 hits the same failure (USERFAULTFD=y).

Fix: validate uffd ranges with MMUPAGE_MASK.  At CONFIG_PAGE_MMUSHIFT
== 0 the two masks are identical and behaviour is byte-for-byte
unchanged.

Verified: s390x PGCL=4 guard-regions: FAIL (2 uffd subtests) → PASS.
Test Summary 86 passed / 1 failed (mkdirty still fails on UFFDIO_COPY
— separate issue, follow-up).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 fs/userfaultfd.c | 13 +++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/fs/userfaultfd.c b/fs/userfaultfd.c
index 4b53dc4a3266..bd2059a511e9 100644
--- a/fs/userfaultfd.c
+++ b/fs/userfaultfd.c
@@ -1234,7 +1234,16 @@ static __always_inline int validate_unaligned_range(
 {
 	__u64 task_size = mm->task_size;
 
-	if (len & ~PAGE_MASK)
+	/*
+	 * Userfaultfd is a userspace-visible interface; ranges are measured
+	 * in the userspace page size, which is MMUPAGE_SIZE under PGCL
+	 * (PAGE_MMUSHIFT > 0).  Without this, mmap'd 10 * sysconf(PAGESIZE)
+	 * = 10 * MMUPAGE_SIZE is rejected as not PAGE_MASK-aligned, breaking
+	 * any uffd consumer that uses sub-PAGE-aligned ranges (e.g. the
+	 * tools/testing/selftests/mm/guard-regions.c uffd subtest).
+	 * At PAGE_MMUSHIFT == 0 the two masks coincide; no change.
+	 */
+	if (len & ~MMUPAGE_MASK)
 		return -EINVAL;
 	if (!len)
 		return -EINVAL;
@@ -1250,7 +1259,7 @@ static __always_inline int validate_unaligned_range(
 static __always_inline int validate_range(struct mm_struct *mm,
 					  __u64 start, __u64 len)
 {
-	if (start & ~PAGE_MASK)
+	if (start & ~MMUPAGE_MASK)
 		return -EINVAL;
 
 	return validate_unaligned_range(mm, start, len);
-- 
